The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 8: Vehicle sales in the country slowed down in November, growing 17.81 per cent against 45.93 per cent in October. According to the Society of Indian Automobile Manufacturers, total number of vehicles sold in the country stood at 12,21,981 units in November this year against 10,37,232 units in the same month last year.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 8: The government has approved signing of agreements to import natural gas through the US-backed Turkmenistan-Afghanistan-Pakistan-India pipeline (TAPI), whose terms are far less stringent than those it had set for another proposed pipeline involving Iran.                             
	 Mumbai, Dec. 8: There will be a common all-India entrance test for public sector bank jobs from next year. The move is aimed at reducing the time and hassles in the recruitment process.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 8: NTPC has earmarked Rs 1,50,000 crore investment for sourcing equipment for its power projects in the next fiscal. We will place orders for equipment next fiscal...deliveries will be for five years, chairman Arup Roy Choudhary said.                                                                                                                          
